09/21/82  read_mail request:  next

Syntax:  next {-control_arg}


Syntax as an active request:  [next {-control_arg}]


Function:  prints the message number of the first message of the
specified type after the current message; as an active request, returns
the message number.


Control arguments:
-include_deleted, -idl
   prints or returns the message number of the first message after the
   current message whether or not it has been deleted.
-only_deleted, -odl
   prints or returns the message number of the first deleted message
   after the current message.
-only_non_deleted, -ondl
   prints or returns the message number of the first non-deleted
   message after the current message.  (Default)


Notes:
If there are no messages of the specified type or there is no current
message, the active request will return the value zero.
